   FILMS: The National Geographic Society reached an
agreement with Imax Systems Corp. jointly to produce
giant-screen films and educational materials. The first film
is scheduled to be released in the fall of 1991. National
Geographic for 25 years has produced shows for television.
                                                                                                       

</LP>
<TEXT>
   RADIO: Shamrock Broadcasting Inc., a unit of Shamrock
Holdings Inc., signed a letter of intent to sell its KMGC-FM
radio station in Dallas to Alliance Broadcasting Inc. Terms
weren't disclosed.
                                                                                                       

   WHO'S NEWS: Nikki Rocco was named to the newly created
post of senior vice president of distribution and marketing
liaison for MCA Inc.'s Universal Pictures unit. She was vice
president of Universal Pictures's distribution division.
